						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Mukti-Kōṭīśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1457, Manmatha, Chaitra śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1535 A.D., March 19, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It refers to the gift of land for the daily worship of the god [Kō]ṭīśvaradēva by Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Salakārāju Tirumalayyadēva mahārāju. Further, it refers to Nārayya, the Kāryakartta of the chief, who must have issued the orders at the instance of his master.</p>						

						</summary>
